These are the domains that transition to container_var_lib_t or container_var_run_t.

Two domains that Podman are likely to run under are unconfined_t and container_runtime_t.

```
ramalama (chat) $ sesearch -T -s unconfined_t | grep " containers"
type_transition unconfined_t var_lib_t:dir container_var_lib_t containers;
type_transition unconfined_t var_run_t:dir container_var_run_t containers;
ramalama (chat) $ sesearch -T -s container_runtime_t | grep " containers"
type_transition container_runtime_t etc_t:dir container_config_t containers;
type_transition container_runtime_t var_lib_t:dir container_var_lib_t containers;
type_transition container_runtime_t var_run_t:dir container_var_run_t containers;
type_transition container_runtime_t var_t:dir container_var_lib_t containers;
```
The issue would be if the top directory was created with tmp_t or user_tmp_t, then this transition would not happen.

We should probbaly add a transition rule for user_tmp_t as well as var_run_t.
